

Notebook mode:

1) Set up regions that tell where input/output cells are.
Regular Input cells:  (^LIn Beg 123^J ... ^LIn End 123^J)
Regular Output cells: (^LOut Beg 123^J ... ^LOut End 123^J)
	
Data cell: (^Ldata beg 123^J ... ^Ldata end 123^J)

2) Typing within a cell gets sent to program. (with cell address.)

3) yanking/pasting/etc. gets sent to program.

4) Set up cells which are arrays.

5) separate program v.s. i/o vs. data section?

6) Color code:
	comments and text.
	input cell (unentered).
	input cell (entered, but not yet processed.)
	input cell (entered, currently processing.)
	input cell (entered and processed)
	input cell (syntax error)
	output cell (read only)
	output cell (read/write)

7) Useful commands:	
	Enter current input cell, and tab to next.
	Tab to next input cell (create new one if none exists). 
	Create new input cell.
	Create output cell at point, input at mark.
	
	
	
8) Output cells:  Usually, a new cell is created right after an input
cell is created.  





